      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>Certificate, dated 3 October 1853, stating that America
         Wood of Albemarle County, "a woman of color," produced
         evidence that she was born free. She is noted as the daughter
         of Mary Shelton, whose mother was born free "previous to
         1806."</p>
